nodes.title: LCM Sampler Step and CFG
widgets_values:
Sampler Steps - Use Steps between 6-12. Default is 8.

Sampler CFG - Use Between 1-5, You can try higher values up to 6 for good results.  You can also test out with different animatediff motion models for different results.

LCM Lora Strength - 0.65 seems good, you can experiment with higher values, also balance CFG and steps.

-------------------------------

*Background still gets messy, use low cfg for good background

*Value of cfg below 4 causes some faded look. You can experiment with 
1) LCM Lora Strength 
2) Sampler Steps
3) Sampler CFG 

All three are dependent on each other.

nodes.title: #4 AnimateDiff Face Fix - LCM v2.1
widgets_values:
[Optional] If you don't have faces in your video, or faces are looking good you can skip this workflow 

If you see face flicker in your refiner pass, you can use this workflow again to reduce the flickering just update the input and output folders.

HOW TO USE: 

After you have refined the Images in #3 AnimateDiff Refiner, 

1) Enter the Paths in Purple Directory Nodes of the Refined Images from #3
2) Enter the Output path for saving them
3) Enter Batch Range for face fix, you can try to put all images (Enter the total number of input images), in one go as only face area will be rendered so Ram will be free. (took only about 6gb vram for 350 images, 2GB free but took 2 hours to render)

4) Skip Frame is 0 by default (Ignore if you put all images in batch range)
5) Use Batch Number Naming for Organizing.


6) Enter Refiner Denoise (0.4 is default and good) 
Sampler First Refines the image then applies Face Fix denoise. 

7) Enter Face Fix Denoise value, it should be around 0.25 - 0.45 for best results. 0.4 is default.
(artifacts, sliding can be seen around neck and detection edges, use lower values if you see any) or you can use lower values and again use this workflow to refine the faces)


8) Enter Prompts for face only, for more accuracy.  
9) Choose Model checkpoint you want to use.


You can Use this face fix pass for any video. Even from old workflows or SVD, just extract frames and it run through this face fixer.



Huge Thanks for @aelemar7888 for giving idea for this face fix workflow.

nodes.title: AnimateDiff
widgets_values:
Model - motionModel_v01 and Temporaldiff-v1-animatediff was seen to produce best results.

Context Length to 16
----------------------------

motionModel_v01 - https://civitai.com/models/139237?modelVersionId=154097

Temporaldiff - https://huggingface.co/CiaraRowles/TemporalDiff/tree/main
* Temporal Diff can sometime give yellow tint to the final image, which can be fixed in post using curves>playing with the blue channel or use 2.5 - 4 cfg.


Feel free to test out other motion models.
